data.name: Caprese Burger
data.quickTastyDescription: A juicy beef burger topped with fresh mozzarella, ripe tomatoes, and basil, drizzled with balsamic glaze for a burst of flavor.
detailedCookingInstructions: Preheat your grill or stovetop pan over medium-high heat.
Season the beef patties with salt and black pepper on both sides.
Cook the patties on the grill or pan for about 4-5 minutes on each side or until they reach your desired doneness.
During the last minute of cooking, place a slice of fresh mozzarella on each patty to melt slightly.
Toast the burger buns lightly on the grill or in a toaster.
Assemble the burger: place the beef patty with melted mozzarella on the bottom bun, add tomato slices, fresh basil leaves, and drizzle with balsamic glaze before placing the top bun on.
data.detailedName: Caprese Burger with Mozzarella, Tomatoes, and Basil
